# Testing rules

- Add tests for every behavior change.
- Use JUnit 5 and AssertJ.
- Use Mockito only at external boundaries.
- Prefer parameterized tests for configuration combinations.
- Use Testcontainers for Kafka integration tests.
- Do not mock KafkaProducer when an integration test is required.
- Test success, failure, boundary, and shutdown behavior.
- Tests must not depend on execution order.
- Tests must not use real corporate infrastructure.
- Use temporary directories for CSV and summary tests.
- Maintain separate Maven profiles for SSL, mTLS, and GSSAPI tests when extra infrastructure is required.
- Use ArchUnit to enforce package dependency direction.
- Run `./mvnw clean verify` before completion.
- Do not disable quality gates to obtain a passing build.
